ling event\n| name=Thanksgiving Star Wars (1986)\n| image=\n| promotion=[[World Class Wrestling Association]]\n| date=November 27, 1986<ref name=ThanksStarWars>{{cite web | url=http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/usa/misc/wccw/starwars.html#thanks86 | title=Thanksgiving Star Wars | date=November 27, 1986 | publisher=Pro Wrestling History}}</ref>\n| venue=[[Reunion Arena]]<ref name=ThanksStarWars/>\n| city=[[Dallas, Texas]]<ref name=ThanksStarWars/>\n| attendance=6,000<ref name=ThanksStarWars/>\n| liveevent=y\n| lastevent = [[WCCW Cotton Bowl Extravaganza#3rd Cotton Bowl Extravaganza|3rd Cotton Bowl Extravaganza]]\n| nextevent = [[#Christmas Star Wars|Christmas Star Wars]]\n| event = [[WCWA Star Wars]]\n| lastevent2 = [[#Labor Day Star Wars|Labor Day]]\n| nextevent2 = [[#Christmas Star Wars|Christmas]]\n}}\n'''Thanksgiving Star Wars (1986)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[supercard]] show that was held on November 27, 1986. The show was produced and scripted by the Dallas, Texas based [[World Class Wrestling Association]] (WCWA) [[professional wrestling promotion]] and held in their home area, Dallas, Texas. Several matches from the show were taped for WCWA's television shows and broadcast in the weeks following the show. The show was the 25th overall show in the \"[[Wrestling Star Wars]]\" event chronology. The show, held at the [[Reunion Arena]], drew 6,000 spectators out of its approximately 21,000 seat capacity.\n\n===Results===\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref name=Almanac86/><ref name=ThanksStarWars/>\n|times=\n\n|match1=[[Scott Casey]] defeated [[Killer Tim Brooks]]\n|stip1=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time1=&nbsp;\n\n|match2=[[Bam Bam Bigalow|Crusher Yurkoff]] (C) wrestled [[Steve Simpson (wrestler)|Steve Simpson]] to a time limit draw\n|stip2=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]] for the [[WCWA Television Championship]]\n|time2=15:00\n\n|match3=[[The Ultimate Warrior|The Dingo Warrior]] defeated [[George Wells (wrestler)|Master Gee]]\n|stip3=[[Professional wrestling match types#Strap match|Chain match]]\n|time3=&nbsp;\n\n|match4=[[Mike Von Erich]] defeated [[Brian Adias]] by disqualification\n|stip4=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time4=&nbsp;\n\n|match5=[[Abdullah the Butcher]] defeated [[Tony Atlas]] by disqualification\n|stip5=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time5=&nbsp;\n\n|match6= [[Kevin Von Erich]] (C) defeated [[Black Bart (wrestler)|Black Bart]]\n|stip6=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]] for the [[WCWA World Heavyweight Championship]]\n|time6=&nbsp;\n\n|match7=[[Lance Von Erich|Lance]] and [[Mike Von Erich]] defeated [[Brian Adias]] and [[Matt Borne]]\n|stip7=[[Tag team match]]\n|time7=&nbsp;\n\n|match8=[[Kevin Von Erich]] defeated [[Al Madril]]\n|stip8=[[No disqualification match|\"Lights Out\" match]]\n|time8=&nbsp;\n\n|match9=[[Fritz Von Erich]] defeated [[Abdullah the Butcher]] by disqualification\n|stip9=[[Professional wrestling match types#Submission match|Submission match]]\n|time9=&nbsp;\n\n}}\n\n==Christmas Star Wars==\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n| name=Christmas Star Wars (1986)\n| image=\n| promotion=[[World Class Wrestling Association]]\n| date=December 25, 1986<ref name=XMasStarWars>{{cite web | url=http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/usa/misc/wccw/starwars.html#xmas86 | title=Christmas Star Wars | date=December 25, 1986 | publisher=Pro Wrestling History}}</ref>\n| venue=[[Reunion Arena]]<ref name=XMasStarWars/>\n| city=[[Dallas, Texas]]<ref name=XMasStarWars/>\n| attendance=7,000<ref name=XMasStarWars/>\n| liveevent=y\n| event = [[WCWA Star Wars]]\n| lastevent2 = [[#Thanksgiving Star Wars|Thanksgiving]]\n| nextevent2 = [[WCWA Star Wars (1987)#Wrestling Star Wars (February)|February 1987]]\n}}\n'''Christmas Star Wars (1986)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[supercard]] show that was held on December 25, 1986. The show was produced and scripted by the Dallas, Texas based [[World Class Wrestling Association]] (WCWA) [[professional wrestling promotion]] and held in their home area, Dallas, Texas. Several matches from the show were taped for WCWA's television shows and broadcast in the weeks following the show. The show was the 26th overall show in the \"[[Wrestling Star Wars]]\" event chronology. The show, held at the [[Reunion Arena]], drew 7,000 spectators out of its approximately 21,000 seat capacity.\n\n===Results===\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref name=Almanac86/><ref name=XMasStarWars/>\n|times=\n\n|match1=[[Mark Youngblood]] defeated [[Killer Tim Brooks]]\n|stip1=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time1=&nbsp;\n\n|match2=[[Steve Simpson (wrestler)|Steve Simpson]] defeated [[Len Denton|The Grappler]]\n|stip2=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time2=&nbsp;\n\n|match3=[[Lance Von Erich]] defeated [[George Wells (wrestler)|Master Gee]]\n|stip3=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3=&nbsp;\n\n|match4=[[The Ultimate Warrior|The Dingo Warrior]] wrestled to a double disqualification against [[Bob Bradley]]\n|stip4=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time4=&nbsp;\n\n|match5=[[Candi Divine]] defeated Lock\n|stip5=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time5=&nbsp;\n\n|match6=[[Tony Atlas]] defeated [[Matt Borne]]\n|stip6=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time6=&nbsp;\n\n|match7=[[Scott Casey]] defeated [[Black Bart (wrestler)|Black Bart]]\n|stip7=\"Loser rides a mule\" match\n|time7=&nbsp;\n\n|match8=[[Kevin Von Erich|Kevin]] and [[Mike Von Erich]] defeated [[Brian Adias]] and [[Al Madril]] (c) by disqualification\n|stip8=[[Tag team match]] for the [[WCWA World Tag Team Championship]] \n|time8=&nbsp;\n\n|match9=[[Abdullah the Butcher]] defeated [[Bruiser Brody]]\n|stip9=[[Steel Cage Match|Loser leaves town steel cage match]]\n|time9=13:47\n\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{World Class Championship Wrestling}}\n{{Portal bar|Texas}}\n\n[[Category:1986 in professional wrestling]]\n[[Category:World Class Championship Wrestling shows]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Professional wrestling show series}}\n[[World Class Championship Wrestling|World Class Wrestling Association]] (WCWA), based out of [[Dallas, Texas]] held a number of major [[professional wrestling]] super shows under the name '''Wrestling Star Wars'' between 1981 and 1989, with five of these being held in 1986.\n\n==Wrestling Star Wars (January)==\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n| name=Wrestling Star Wars (January 1986)\n| image=\n| promotion=[[World Class Championship Wrestling]]\n| date=January 26, 1986<ref name=StarWars0186>{{cite web | url=http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/usa/misc/wccw/miscsw.html#0186 | title=Wrestling Star Wars | date=January 26, 1986 | publisher=Pro Wrestling History}}</ref>\n| venue=[[Fort Worth Convention Center|The Convention Center]]<ref name=StarWars0186/>\n| city=[[Ft. Worth, Texas]]<ref name=StarWars0186/>\n| attendance=8,100<ref name=StarWars0186/>\n| liveevent=y\n| lastevent = [[WCCW Star Wars (1985)#Christmas Star Wars|Christmas Star Wars]]\n| nextevent = [[Parade of Champions#3rd Von Erich Memorial Parade of Champions|3rd Von Erich Memorial Parade of Champions]]\n| event = [[WCWA Star Wars]]\n| lastevent2 = [[WCCW Star Wars (1985)#Christmas Star Wars|Christmas]]\n| nextevent2 = [[#Independence Day Star Wars|Independence Day]]\n}}\n'''Wrestling Star Wars (January 1986)''' was a [[professional wrestling]] [[supercard]] show that was held on January 26, 1986. The show was produced and scripted by the Dallas, Texas based [[World Class Championship Wrestling]] (WCCW) [[professional wrestling promotion]] and held in their home area, Dallas/Ft. Worth, Texas. Several matches from the show were taped for WCCW's television shows and broadcast in the weeks following the show. The show was the 22nd overall show in the \"[[Wrestling Star Wars]]\" event chronology. The show, held at the [[Fort Worth Convention Center]], drew 8,100 spectators out if its estimated 18,000 seat capacity when configured for professional wrestling shows.\n\n===Results===\n{{Pro Wrestling results table\n|results=<ref name=StarWars0186/><ref name=Almanac86>{{cite news|title=Historical Cards: Christmas Star Wars (December 25, 1982. Dallas, Texas) |work=PWI Presents: 2007 Wrestling Almanak and book of facts |publisher=Kappa Publications|id=2007 Edition|page=174}}</ref>\n|times=\n\n|match1=Jerry Allen defeated Tommy Montana\n|stip1=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time1=\n\n|match2=[[Chris Adams (wrestler)|Chris Adams]] defeated [[Gino Hernandez]] by disqualification\n|stip2=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time2=\n\n|match3=[[Mark Youngblood]] defeated [[Jack Victory]]\n|stip3=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time3=\n\n|match4=[[Iceman Parsons]] and [[The Missing Link (wrestler)|The Missing Link]] defeated [[Rick Rude]] and [[Len Denton|The Grappler]]\n|stip4=[[Tag team match]]\n|time4=\n\n|match6=[[John Tatum (wrestler)|John Tatum]] defeated [[Brian Adias]]\n|stip6=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time6=\n\n|match7=[[Bruiser Brody]], [[Kerry Von Erich|Kerry]] and [[Lance Von Erich]] defeated The [[Fabulous Freebirds]] ([[Michael Hayes (wrestler)|Michael Hayes]], [[Terry Gordy]] and [[Buddy Roberts]]) (c) by disqualification\n|stip7=[[Six-man tag team match]] for the [[WCWA Six-Man Tag Team Championship]] \n|time7=\n\n|match8=[[Sunshine (wrestling)|Sunshine]] defeated [[Missy Hyatt]] via countout.\n|stip8=[[Singles match (professional wrestling)|Singles match]]\n|time8=\n\n|match9=[[Bruiser Brody]] defeated [[One Man Gang]]\n|stip9=[[Steel Cage Match|steel cage chain match]]\n|time9=\n\n}}\n\n==Independence Day Star Wars==\n{{Infobox Wrestling event\n| name=Independence Day Star Wars (1986)\n|