cully in 2015\n| birth_name = Peter Gerard Scully<ref name=\"SMH bground\">{{Cite web |last1= Mills |first1= Tammy |last2= Vedelago |first2= Chris |last3= Murdoch |first3= Lindsay |date= 6 March 2015 |title= Alleged pedophile Peter Gerard Scully fled a sordid past in Melbourne |url= http://www.smh.com.au/national/alleged-paedophile-peter-gerard-scully-fled-a-sordid-past-in-melbourne-20150306-13x5m8.html |work= [[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170719064850/http://www.smh.com.au/national/alleged-paedophile-peter-gerard-scully-fled-a-sordid-past-in-melbourne-20150306-13x5m8.html |archive-date= 19 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1963|01|13}}\n| birth_place = [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], Australia\n| nationality = Australian\n| conviction_status = Convicted\n| charge = Human trafficking, rape\n| criminal_penalty = [[Life sentence]]\n| apprehended = 20 February 2015\n| imprisoned = [[The Philippines]]\n}}\n\n'''Peter Gerald Scully''' (born 13 January 1963) is a convicted Australian [[child rapist]] serving a life sentence in prison in the [[Philippines]].  In June 2018, he was found guilty of one count of [[human trafficking]] and five counts of rape.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-06-14/australian-peter-scully-convicted-in-philippines/9868958 | title=Australian Peter Scully given life sentence for human trafficking, rape in Philippines, reports say | website=[[ABC News (Australia)]] | date=14 June 2018| access-date=15 June 2018 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618050524/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-06-14/australian-peter-scully-convicted-in-philippines/9868958 | archive-date=18 June 2018 | url-status=live }}</ref> He is pending trial for other crimes against children including the production and dissemination of [[child pornography]], torture, and the alleged murder of an 11-year-old girl.\n\n== Background ==\nPeter Scully lived in the [[Narre Warren]] suburb of [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]] with his wife and two children prior to fleeing to the [[Manila|City of Manila]], [[Philippines]], in 2011<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.smh.com.au/national/alleged-paedophile-peter-gerard-scully-fled-a-sordid-past-in-melbourne-20150306-13x5m8.html|title=Alleged paedophile Peter Gerard Scully fled a sordid past in Melbourne|first1=Tammy|last1=Mills|first2=Chris|last2=Vedelago|first3=Lindsay|last3=Murdoch|date=6 March 2015|website=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|language=en|access-date=20 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191110122342/https://www.smh.com.au/national/alleged-paedophile-peter-gerard-scully-fled-a-sordid-past-in-melbourne-20150306-13x5m8.html|archive-date=10 November 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> before he could be charged with his involvement in a property scheme that cost investors over $2.68 million. Prior to leaving Victoria, he operated an unlicensed [[escort agency|escort service]] website which offered his Malaysian girlfriend as a prostitute. The [[Australian Securities and Investment Commission]] found him involved in 117 fraud and deception offenses relating to real estate scams from an investigation started in 2009.<ref name=\"SMH bground\"/> From the island of [[Mindanao]], he is alleged to have built up a lucrative international [[Pedophilia|pedophile]] ring that offered [[pay-per-view]] video streams of children being tortured and sexually abused on the [[dark web]]. Among the victims who had their videoed ordeals sold over the Internet was an 18-month-old infant who was hung upside down while Scully and two accomplices raped and tortured her.<ref name=\"NewsAUS deathpen\">{{Cite web |last= Sutton |first= Candace |date= 23 September 2016 |title= Australian child molester Peter Scully faces death penalty in Philippines |url= http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/australian-child-molester-peter-scully-faces-death-penalty-in-philippines/news-story/f15a28a8b971d95f815b5f6105814ff9 |website= news.com.au |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170706100407/http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/australian-child-molester-peter-scully-faces-death-penalty-in-philippines/news-story/f15a28a8b971d95f815b5f6105814ff9 |archive-date= 6 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n\nVictims were procured by Scully with promises to impoverished parents of work, education, or were solicited by his two Filipino girlfriends, Carme Ann Alvarez and Liezyl Margallo,<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\">{{Cite web |last= Murdoch |first= Lindsay |date= 20 September 2016 |title= Death penalty call for accused Australian child sex predator Peter Scully in Philippines |url= http://www.smh.com.au/world/death-penalty-call-for-accused-australian-child-sex-predator-peter-scully-in-philippines-20160920-grk65r.html |work= [[The Sydney Morning Herald]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170703135944/http://www.smh.com.au/world/death-penalty-call-for-accused-australian-child-sex-predator-peter-scully-in-philippines-20160920-grk65r.html |archive-date= 3 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> and other female acquaintances such as Maria Dorothea Chi y Chia.<ref name=\"ABSCBN another\">{{Cite web |last= Mendoza |first= Greanne |date= 17 February 2017 |title= Another suspect linked to Australian sex fiend arrested |url= http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/02/17/17/another-suspect-linked-to-australian-sex-fiend-arrested |website= [[ABS-CBN News and Current Affairs|ABS-CBN News]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170629104700/http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/02/17/17/another-suspect-linked-to-australian-sex-fiend-arrested |archive-date= 29 June 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> Both Alvarez and Margallo also abused children in Scully's videos.\n\nIn 2016, prosecutors in [[Cagayan de Oro|Cagayan de Oro, Philippines]] alleged that Scully and a girlfriend coaxed two teenage girls to come to Scully's house with the promise of food.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" /> Scully was alleged to have given the girls alcohol and forced them to perform sex acts on each other which he photographed and filmed.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" /> The prosecutor alleged that when the girls tried to escape, Scully forced them to dig graves in the basement of the house and threatened that he would bury them there.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" />  After five days, the girls were released by the girlfriend, who began feeling remorse after coming home to see the two in pet collars, and reported what had happened.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" />\n\n=== ''Daisy's Destruction'' ===\nThe most notorious of Scully's output was a video titled ''Daisy's Destruction'', which he sold to clients for up to $10,000.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" /> Made in 2012, the multi-part film is so extreme that it was, for some time, regarded as an [[urban legend]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= Waugh |first= Rob |date= 26 September 2016 |title= What is Daisy's Destruction? 'Snuff film' urban legend actually exists |url= http://metro.co.uk/2016/09/26/what-is-daisys-destruction-snuff-film-urban-legend-actually-exists-6153626/ |publisher= [[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170710095822/http://metro.co.uk/2016/09/26/what-is-daisys-destruction-snuff-film-urban-legend-actually-exists-6153626/ |archive-date= 10 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> It features the torture and brutal rape of a number of girls by Scully and some Filipina accomplices; the three main victims were Liza (aged 12), Cindy (11), and Daisy (18 months).<ref name=\"9news monster\">{{Cite web |last= Brown |first= Tara |authorlink= Tara Brown |title= Catching a monster: The global manhunt for alleged paedophile Peter Gerard Scully |url= http://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/03/16/02/19/tracking-the-australian-man-allegedly-responsible-for-horrific-child-sexual-abuse |website= [[Nine.com.au|9news.com.au]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |date= 16 March 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170709164025/http://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/03/16/02/19/tracking-the-australian-man-allegedly-responsible-for-horrific-child-sexual-abuse |archive-date= 9 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref>  \n\nUrged on by Scully, some of the most severe physical abuse was carried out on the children by one of his girlfriends, then 19-year-old Liezyl Margallo, who was formerly prostituted as a child.<ref>{{Cite web |last1= Alipon |first1= Joworski |last2= Andrade |first2= Angelo |date= 27 January 2017 |title= Filipina behind brutal 'Daisy' sex videos arrested |url= http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/01/27/17/filipina-behind-brutal-daisy-sex-videos-arrested |website= ABS-CBN News |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170625165632/http://news.abs-cbn.com/news/01/27/17/filipina-behind-brutal-daisy-sex-videos-arrested |archive-date= 25 June 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> Indeed, it seems Margallo was the sole hands-on victimizer of Daisy: The introduction to the film invites the viewer to watch Daisy's \"mental ruin\" as she \"learn[s] how to please her mistress\".<ref name=\"60 Mins monster\" />\n\nScully put ''Daisy's Destruction'' out under his \"No Limits Fun\" production company, selling it to other people via the [[dark web]]. Among those who acquired it was one of the biggest-ever purveyors of child pornography, Scully's fellow Australian Matthew David Graham, better known by his online pseudonym Lux. Apprehended at age 22, he ran a series of \"[[hurtcore]]\" child pornography sites.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/lux-captured-the-simple-error-that-brought-down-the-worlds-worst-hurtcore-paedophile-20160513-goum54.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=31 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831184554/http://www.smh.com.au/national/lux-captured-the-simple-error-that-brought-down-the-worlds-worst-hurtcore-paedophile-20160513-goum54.html |archive-date=31 August 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= Dunn |first= Matthew |date= 20 February 2016 |title= FBI describe dark net paedophile kingpin as one of the most prolific child sex offenders ever |url= http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/censorship/fbi-describe-dark-net-paedophile-kingpin-as-one-of-the-most-prolific-child-sex-offenders-ever/news-story/eb468fcdb238a09883a1a6fe3b69d0a2 |website= news.com.au |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170715234936/http://www.news.com.au/technology/online/censorship/fbi-describe-dark-net-paedophile-kingpin-as-one-of-the-most-prolific-child-sex-offenders-ever/news-story/eb468fcdb238a09883a1a6fe3b69d0a2 |archive-date= 15 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> Graham said he got the video so he could use it to attract more viewers to his network of websites.\n\n== Arrest and trial ==\nMatthew Graham, with access to the video, uploaded ''Daisy's Destruction'' publicly, thus allowing the general public to view it.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Daly |date=19 February 2018 |first1=Max |title=Inside the Repulsive World of 'Hurtcore', the Worst Crimes Imaginable |url=https://www.vice.com/en_au/article/59kye3/the-repulsive-world-of-hurtcore-the-worst-crimes-imaginable |website=Vice |accessdate=29 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231045831/https://www.vice.com/en_au/article/59kye3/the-repulsive-world-of-hurtcore-the-worst-crimes-imaginable |archive-date=31 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> After the surfacing of ''Daisy's Destruction'', the Dutch National Child Exploitation Team was the first to open an investigation, with the goal of locating the victims. Subsequently, an international manhunt for those responsible for the video's production was launched. Scully was eventually tracked to [[Malaybalay|Malaybalay City]] in the Philippines and arrested on 20 February 2015. Investigators had six warrants for his arrest,<ref name=\"60 Mins monster\">{{Cite episode |title= Catching a Monster <!-- |access-date= 4 November 2018 --> |series= [[60 Minutes (Australian TV program)|60 Minutes]] |first= Tara |last= Brown |network= [[Nine News]] |station= |date= 2015 |season= |series-no= |number= |minutes= |time= |transcript= |transcript-url= |quote= |language=}} [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YI33EPlCW5w Part 1] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414231019/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YI33EPlCW5w |date=14 April 2019 }} - [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9MftNB12leI Part 2] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107210041/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9MftNB12leI&gl=US&hl=en&has_verified=1&bpctr=9999999999 |date=7 November 2019 }}</ref> all relating to the abduction and sexual abuse of the two cousins.<ref name=\"SMH deathpen\" />{{failed verification|date=June 2019}} While they searched for Scully in the Philippines, investigators managed to uncover the fates of the three primary victims in ''Daisy's Destruction''. Liza was found to be alive, as was Daisy, though her treatment had been so vicious that she has lasting physical injuries. Eleven-year-old Cindy had been murdered, allegedly by Scully. Before being strangled to death with a rope, the girl was subjected to bouts of rape and torture, and was made to dig her own grave. According to Margallo,<!-- she may have claimed this to help explain how she knew of the details about Cindy's murder (\"Scully showed me the video, that's how I know&nbsp;...\" --> Scully videotaped himself killing Cindy.<ref name=\"60 Mins monster\" />\n\nScully faced a total of 75 charges. He was on trial with others who assisted in the production of his pornography, including four men&nbsp;\u2014 Germany's Christian Rouche, Filipinos Alexander Lao and Althea Chia and a Brazilian doctor, Haniel Caetano de Oliveira.<ref name=\"NewsAUS deathpen\" /><ref>{{Cite web |last= Reformina |first= Ina |date= 6 March 2015 |title= Australian behind 'Daisy' sex videos charged |url= http://news.abs-cbn.com/nation/03/06/15/australian-behind-daisy-sex-videos-charged |website= ABS-CBN News |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170715014858/http://news.abs-cbn.com/nation/03/06/15/australian-behind-daisy-sex-videos-charged |archive-date= 15 July 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last1= Rocha |first1= Alex |last2= Idal\u00f3 |first2= Eduardo |date= 21 December 2015 |title= M\u00e9dico de Uberaba admite pedofilia e se diz doente, segundo PF |url= http://g1.globo.com/minas-gerais/triangulo-mineiro/noticia/2015/12/medico-de-uberaba-admite-relacao-com-pedofilia-e-se-diz-doente-diz-pf.html |language= Portuguese |website= [[Grupo Globo|g1.globo.com]] |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170803085241/http://g1.globo.com/minas-gerais/triangulo-mineiro/noticia/2015/12/medico-de-uberaba-admite-relacao-com-pedofilia-e-se-diz-doente-diz-pf.html |archive-date= 3 August 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n\nIn October 2015, a fire severely damaged the evidence room containing Scully's computer logs and videos, destroying key evidence.<ref name=\"SMH mastermind\">{{Cite web |last= Murdoch |first= Lindsay |date= 31 January 2017 |title= Alleged child abuser Peter Scully 'may still be masterminding porn network' |url= http://www.smh.com.au/world/alleged-child-abuser-peter-scully-may-still-be-masterminding-porn-network-20170131-gu25sw.html |website= smh.com.au |access-date= 11 July 2017 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170626031311/http://www.smh.com.au/world/alleged-child-abuser-peter-scully-may-still-be-masterminding-porn-network-20170131-gu25sw.html |archive-date= 26 June 2017 |url-status= live }}</ref> Some believe Scully may have bribed a local police officer,<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://philippineslifestyle.com/blog/2015/10/09/australian-pedophile-peter-scully-could-walk-free-in-light-of-new-evidence/ | title=Australian child abuser Peter Scully could walk free in light of new evidence | last=Walker | first=Timothy | work=Philippines Lifestyle News | publisher=CWCMedia | date=2015-10-09 | access-date=22 May 2017 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170701164838/http://philippineslifestyle.com/blog/2015/10/09/australian-pedophile-peter-scully-could-walk-free-in-light-of-new-evidence/ | archive-date=1 July 2017 | url-status=live }}</ref> <ref>{{cite web |last1=Cullen |first1=Shay |title=Hungry for justice: Harsh realities of child abuse |url=https://www.rappler.com/views/imho/101130-child-abuse-justice |website=Rappler |language=en |access-date=20 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105044222/https://www.rappler.com/views/imho/101130-child-abuse-justice |archive-date=5 January 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> as [[corruption in the Philippines]] is high.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hawley |first=Samantha |date=10 March 2015 |title=Philippine police expect to arrest more people in case of alleged Australian paedophile Peter Gerard Scully |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-11/philippine-police-prepare-to-arrest-more-paedophile-suspects/6301406 |website=ABC News Online |access-date=11 June 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150606195922/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-11/philippine-police-prepare-to-arrest-more-paedophile-suspects/6301406 |archive-date=6 June 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>{{failed verification|date=August 2018}} On June 13, 2018, Scully, and his girlfriend Alvarez, were sentenced to life in prison.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2018/06/14/infamous-pedophile-smiles-as-he-gets-life-in-prison/|title=Infamous pedophile smiles as he gets life in prison|work=[[New York Post]]|last=Sutton|first=Candance|date=June 14, 2018|accessdate=25 November 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217165504/https://nypost.com/2018/06/14/infamous-pedophile-smiles-as-he-gets-life-in-prison/|archive-date=17 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMargaret Akullo, then Project Coordinator for the [[United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime]] and an expert on child abuse investigations,<ref>[https://www.unodc.org/documents/southeastasiaandpacific/2014/11/vac/Speakers_Facilitators_Trainers_BIO_3-5_Nov_2014.pdf Regional Training Workshop on Responding to Violence against Children in Contact with the Justice System] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170510200257/https://www.unodc.org/documents/southeastasiaandpacific/2014/11/vac/Speakers_Facilitators_Trainers_BIO_3-5_Nov_2014.pdf |date=10 May 2017 }}. 3\u20135 November 2014 conference at United Nations Conference Center, Bangkok, Thailand.</ref> described the case as \"horrific\" and the worst she had ever heard of.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{cite news |author1=Lindsay Murdoch |author2=Chris Vedelago |date=1 March 2015 |title=Peter Gerard Scully made Philippines children dig own grave: victims |newspaper=The Age |publisher=Fairfax Media |url=http://www.theage.com.au/world/peter-gerard-scully-made-philippines-children-dig-own-grave-victims-20150301-13rtke.html |access-date=11 June 2015}}\n*{{cite news |author1=Lindsay Murdoch |author2=Tammy Mills |date=6 March 2015 |title=Execution calls for Melbourne man Peter Gerard Scully accused of depraved acts in the Philippines |newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald |url=http://www.smh.com.au/world/execution-calls-for-melbourne-man-peter-gerard-scully-accused-of-depraved-acts--in-the-philippines-20150305-13vodd.html |access-date=11 June 2015}}\n*{{cite news |last=Escalante |first=Shirley |date=10 March 2015 |title=Australian man Gerard Peter Scully formally charged with murder, child sexual abuse in the Philippines |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-07/australian-man-charged-with-murder-11yo-girl-in-philippines/6287794 |website=ABC News Online |agency=AFP |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ZDg6jKVj |archive-date=11 June 2015 |url-status=live |access-date=11 June 2015}}\n*{{cite news |last=Davey |first=Melissa |date=2 June 2015 |title=Philippines police to mount strong case against accused Australian paedophile |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/02/philippines-police-to-mount-strong-case-against-accused-australian-paedophile |newspaper=The Guardian |access-date=11 June 2015}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Scully, Peter}}\n\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian criminals]]\n[[Category:Australian people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Crime in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:Dark web]]\n[[Category:Australian rapists]]\n[[Category:Australian murderers of children]]\n[[Category:People charged with murder]]\n[[Category:People convicted of child pornography offenses]]\n[[Category:Australian expatriates in the Philippines]]\n", "name_user": "2601:192:8500:f2c:79d4:c36d:c311:f3bd", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Content I found)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Scully"}
